  "script": "This giant lizard doesn't need to win the fight, it just needs one bite. It's the Komodo dragon, and it can grow ten feet long. When it ambushes a water buffalo, it doesn't hold on. It bites once, then backs off and follows. Its mouth carries venom that stops blood from clotting, so the wound never closes. It will trail its prey for days, waiting, until the animal finally collapses from blood loss. Then the whole dragon clan moves in. It's less a hunter and more a patient executioner. So how does something this big stay hidden long enough to strike?",
